## JavaScript Example

```javascript
function calculateTotal(items) {
  return items
    .filter(item => item.price > 0)
    .map(item => item.price * item.quantity)
    .reduce((total, price) => total + price, 0);
}

const cart = [
  { name: 'Product 1', price: 10, quantity: 2 },
  { name: 'Product 2', price: 5, quantity: 4 }
];

console.log(`Total: $${calculateTotal(cart)}`);
```

The JavaScript code above demonstrates a simple shopping cart calculation function.

## CSS Example

```css
.container {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(250px, 1fr));
  gap: 1rem;
  padding: 2rem;
  background-color: var(--bg-primary);
}

.card {
  border-radius: 0.5rem;
  box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
  transition: transform 0.3s ease;
}

.card:hover {
  transform: translateY(-5px);
}
```

The CSS code above shows a basic grid layout with hover effects.

## TypeScript Example

```typescript
interface CartItem {
  name: string;
  price: number;
  quantity: number;
}

class ShoppingCart {
  private items: CartItem[] = [];

  addItem(item: CartItem): void {
    this.items.push(item);
  }

  getTotal(): number {
    return this.items
      .filter(item => item.price > 0)
      .reduce((total, item) => total + (item.price * item.quantity), 0);
  }
}
```

The TypeScript code above demonstrates typed interfaces and classes for a shopping cart implementation.
